# Playbook: Accessibility Audit

## Workflow
Audit → Test → Fix → Verify

## Steps

1. **Audit**
   - Review UI for WCAG 2.2 AA compliance
   - Check semantic HTML usage
   - Verify ARIA usage (only if needed)
   - Check color contrast
   - Review keyboard navigation

2. **Test**
   - Test with screen readers (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver)
   - Verify keyboard navigation
   - Test with keyboard only
   - Check focus management

3. **Fix**
   - Fix semantic HTML issues
   - Add ARIA only when semantic HTML insufficient
   - Fix color contrast issues
   - Improve keyboard navigation
   - Fix focus management

4. **Verify**
   - Re-test with screen readers
   - Verify keyboard navigation works
   - Check color contrast meets standards
   - Final WCAG 2.2 AA compliance check

## Checklist
- Semantic HTML used correctly
- ARIA only when needed
- Keyboard navigation works
- Screen reader compatible
- Color contrast meets WCAG 2.2 AA
- Focus indicators visible
- Focus management correct
